data.title: Student Government - Student Organizations - Kimmel Student Involvement Center
data.text:
Olivia Davila, Financial Officer

Hometown: Silvis, IL

Year in School: Sophomore

Major: Mathematical Studies - Actuarial Science

Vision for Student Government: "I would like to make SG a place where all people can come into the office and feel welcome to share concerns or receive help."

Hobbies: Baking, hanging with my friends and taking care of my house plants!

Other campus involvement: Honors Student Association Phi Eta Sigma Rotaract Club National Residence Hall Honorary Stem Student Ambassador-Research

Contact Me: odavila@siue.edu Britney Wallace, External Affairs Officer

Hometown: Montego Bay, Jamaica

Year in School: Junior

Major: Nursing

Vision for Student Government: "I hope to see student government increasing its outreach on campus and welcoming more student feedback. I would like SIUE students to feel comfortable with coming to student government with any concerns they have. I want student government to have a positive impact in making SIUE a great place to continue higher education in a safe and judgement free environment."

Hobbies: I really enjoy going to my local bookstore and grabbing a good book. I love drinking coffee and you will often find me in a cafe with a cup. I also enjoy catching up on my favorite TV shows.

Other Campus Involvement: School of Nursing Diversity Board, Resident Housing Association, Resident Assistant, Community Nursing Fellowship for the SON, Student Nurse Achievement Program (SNAP).

Contact Me: britnwa@siue.edu Kaia ford, Internal Affairs Officer

Hometown: Prairie City, IL

Year in School: 1st Year Graduate student

Major: Industrial/Organizational Psychology

Vision for Student Government: "As the Internal Affairs Officer, I would like to make the Student Government office as inviting and welcoming as possible to the student body as well as the officers within the organization. I want to help advertise all of the events that Student Government has to offer in an effort to make the accomplishments from Student Government more heard of.

Hobbies: In my free time, I like to go on walks, watch movies, read, cook new recipes, and spend time with my two kitties, Thor and Cannoli.

Other campus involvement: Graduate Assistant

Contact Me: kfordaa@siue.edu Kaelyn Cupil, Student Wellness & Equity Officer

Hometown: Chicago, IL

Year in School: Senior

Major: Nursing

Vision for Student Government: I want the majority of SIUE’s students to know what Student Government does, know the people on it that represent them, and have faith we’ll get the job done when needed.

Hobbies: Singing, painting, writing…anything that keeps me from having to check my email!

Other campus involvement: Student Nurse Achievement Program (SNAP) President SIUE Gospel Choir President Black Student Union (BSU) Secretary

Contact Me: kcupil@siue.edu

Benjamin Cole, Freshman Senator

Hometown: Moro, IL

Year in School: Freshman

Major: PhysicsVision for Student Government: One thing people always say is, I wish I did that freshmen year. I plan on making sure no SIUE student will ever say that again. Getting the freshmen class involved and solving any issues that stand in our way is my main objective for the following year. College is an important transition in our lives, so nobody can be left behind, as it is our jobs to reach our full potential and push our peers to theirs.Hobbies: I like to stay busy from waking to bedtime. In my free time though, I love working out, doing any outdoor activities (expect climbing), being with family, talking to the residents at the nursing home I work at, 한국어를 공부하다, and many basic nerdy things. I also enjoy meeting new people! If you get me going, I will not stop talking.Other campus involvement: Honors Student AssociationContact Me: becole@SIUE.edu
